<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880810-0165 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business: California Energy Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> NRG </CO><TEXT>   CALIFORNIA ENERGY CO., San Francisco, said it received a $150 million loan from Credit Suisse Bank to help its 47.6%-controlled partnership build more generating units at the Coso Hot Springs geothermal power plant. The developer of geothermal energy and power said the loan will help finance the fourth, fifth and sixth generating units of the power plant in Inyo County, Calif. The $500 million, 230-megawatt generating plant has one of its nine proposed units in operation. Four are under construction and are expected to be completed by year's end. The company said the entire plant should be completed by the end of 1989. The company said it expects the plant to generate revenue of nearly $4 million a month by the first quarter of next year. The energy will be sold mostly to consumers in Southern California, the company said. </TEXT></DOC>